## Quickstart

```bash
mise install                                   # install pinned tools (node, pnpm, pulumi)
mise run install                               # install infra dependencies
gcloud auth application-default login          # authenticate with ADC (no key files)

cd infra
pulumi stack select dev                        # or: pulumi stack init dev
mise run infra:preview                         # see what would change (read-only)
```

Never commit a service-account key. Local runs use Application Default Credentials; CI uses
Workload Identity Federation. See [AGENTS.md](./AGENTS.md) → **Deploying**.

## Layout

| Path | What |
|---|---|
| `infra/` | The Pulumi program (TypeScript) |
| `infra/index.ts` | Stack entry point — wires config + components, exports outputs |
| `infra/src/components/` | Reusable `ComponentResource` building blocks (secure GCS bucket example) |
| `infra/src/config.ts` | Pure, unit-tested config helpers (region/labels) |
| `infra/policy/` | CrossGuard policy pack — deploy-time guardrails |
| `infra/Pulumi.{dev,prod}.yaml` | Per-environment stack config (no secrets committed) |
| `specs/` | Spec-driven workflow artifacts (see `specs/README.md`) |
| `.forge/manifest.json` | WellForge generation manifest (upgrade contract) |

## Commands

| Command | What it does |
|---|---|
| `mise run install` | Install dependencies |
| `mise run build` | Compile-check the program (`tsc --noEmit`) |
| `mise run test` | Unit tests (Pulumi mocks) |
| `mise run lint` | Biome check |
| `mise run dev` | `pulumi preview` for the current stack |
| `mise run infra:up` | Apply changes to the current stack |
| `mise run infra:policy` | Preview with the CrossGuard policy pack enforced |

